sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K332034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Constitutive promoter + 37℃ induced RBS + tetR + double terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: the 37℃ induced RBS is from iGEM08_TUDelft
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
To regulate following genes by temperature.
To maintain cells at 37?? C ↑ : the tetR protein be generated and repress Ptet's circuit.
To release cells at 37?? C ↓ : the tetR protein not be generated and do not repress Ptet's circuit. The theoretical switching temperature of BBa_k115002, which was designed by Team TUDelft in 2008, is 37℃.
Thus, our thermosensing device A can be induced at this temperature. (The switching temperature can be modified by changing RBS according to different conditions.)
Once being swiched on, tetR will inhibit the corresponding promoter, pTet, which enables us to regulate the expression of cry gene and quorum sensing gene devices.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: To regulate following genes by temperature.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: KUO, CHIA-CHUN

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Constitutive promoter + 37℃ induced RBS + tetR + double terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: we took advantage of the interaction between 37?? C induced RBS, tetR gene and pTet promoter to create the temperature regulating circuit. The following is a description of our prescribed strategy. First, we use the constitutive promoter, 37?? C induced RBS (K115002), the tetR gene and terminators. We will call this part the ???Regulator???. We speculate that when the ???Regulator??? and ???Production??? sections are combined, we can achieve a high bacteria growth rate and close to no target protein producing rate at T>37??C, and low bacteria growth rate and high target protein producing rate at T<37??C.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tetR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the TetR protein without the Ribosome Binding Site. Modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein and faster fall time for the emission. TetR binds to the pTet regulator (BBa_R0040). aTc (anhydrotetracycline) binds to TetR and inhibits its operation.

BBa_C0040 TetR Protein is based on the TetR sequence from Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.
